properties.headline: Lakeshore Flood Advisory issued January 5 at 4:37AM EST until January 6 at 12:00PM EST by NWS Marquette MI
properties.description:
The National Weather Service in Marquette has issued a Lakeshore
Flood Advisory...which is in effect from midnight tonight to noon
EST Monday.

* Winds...From the northwest at 30 to 40 mph with gusts up to 45
mph possible, becoming west by late morning Monday.

* Waves...12 to 15 feet. The highest waves are expected early
Monday morning from east of Munising to Crisp Point.

* Impacts...Minor lakeshore flooding and beach and shoreline
erosion are expected.
properties.instruction:
A Lakeshore Flood Advisory indicates that onshore winds and waves
will generate flooding of low areas along the lakeshore.

NWSheadline: LAKESHORE FLOOD ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM MIDNIGHT TONIGHT TO NOON EST MONDAY
